Transcriptomics and the analysis of RNA-Seq data
================

## Read our data for today

``` r
counts <- read.csv("airway_scaledcounts.csv", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
metadata <-  read.csv("airway_metadata.csv", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)
```

We will compare the control vs treated count data contained in `counts`
object.

We will first extract the control columns by looking up their colnames
in the `metadata` object.

<Control>

``` r
#metadata
#metadata$dex == "control"

# Access just the "control" metadata
control <- metadata[metadata$dex == "control",]
control
```

+2 as *upregulated* and less than -2 as *downregulated*.
